snippet.title: GOAT LEG FEET | Cooking & Eating in Village | Healthy Goat Leg Recipe | Traditional Mutton Recipes
snippet.description:
For this recipe, we used 100 goat leg feet. Goat legs contain bone, skin, and hair, so we cleaned them with hot water. After cleaning, we boiled the mutton leg feet, and finally, we cooked them with our traditional method. 
Usually, goat leg feet are used for mutton paya or bone soup, but we cook it as gravy. We enjoy this recipe on a rainy evening.

snippet.title: Maharashtra Bandh की पूरी जानकारी, घर से निकलने से पहले इसवीडियो को देखें I Badlapur News | SN
snippet.description:
#breakingnews #hindinews 
Maharashtra Bandh News : महाराष्‍ट्र के ठाणे जिले में
स्थित बदलापुर में स्‍कूल में बच्चियों से यौन उत्‍पीड़न के बाद फैली
हिंसा पर अब राज्‍य में राजनीति भी जमकर होने लगी है. शिवसेना (यूबीटी)
के चीफ उद्धव ठाकरे ने गुरुवार को इस घटना के विरोधी में 24 अगस्त को

snippet.title: Exploring Bandra with Raghav Juyal | Tere Gully Mein Ep 79 | Curly Tales
snippet.description:
In this episode of Tere Gully Mein, we’re joined by the king of slow-motion dance & now a rising star in the world of acting, killing it on screen quite literally these days!

We had a blast exploring Bandra with Raghav on a rainy day, all while cruising in the bold, stylish, and oh-so-comfortable All New Honda Elevate.

Our adventure began at Imlee, the ultimate chaat gully by CurlyTales, where Raghav took on the challenge of eating pani puri in slow motion. We also savored some mouthwatering pav bhaji and Haridwar’s famous kadhi chawal. Being the foodie he is, Raghav absolutely loved every bite! We even enjoyed Vrindavan’s famous lassi right in the car.

Next up was Mutuswami Cafe, where we indulged in a giant paper dosa, idli, vada, and more. The day was truly a feast for the senses!

Throughout the episode, Raghav opened up about his journey in the entertainment industry, his life in Dehradun, his love for food and travel, and his exciting series Gyaarah Gyaarah.

If you enjoyed this episode, don’t forget to drop a comment below!
